<body>

<header>
    <h1>Memorandum: Invisible Two-Column Tables for Signature Blocks</h1>
</header>

<div class="container">
    <div class="section">
        <h2>To: Legal Clinic Staff</h2>
        <h2>From: Nolan Silverstein</h2>
        <h2>Date: 2/24/2025</h2>
        <h2>Subject: Creating Invisible Two-Column Tables for Signature Blocks</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Purpose</h2>
        <p>This memorandum provides instructions on how to create an invisible two-column table in Microsoft Word to format signature blocks professionally and consistently.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Step 1: Insert a Two-Column Table</h2>
        <ul class="steps">
            <li>Place your cursor where you want the signature block.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Insert</strong> > <strong>Table</strong>.</li>
            <li>Select <strong>2 Columns and 1 Row</strong>.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Step 2: Adjust Column Widths</h2>
        <ul class="steps">
            <li>Click inside the table.</li>
            <li>Move the cursor to the boundary between the columns until the double-arrow icon appears.</li>
            <li>Drag the column width to provide adequate space for both signatures.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Step 3: Enter Signature Information</h2>
        <ul class="steps">
            <li>In the left column, type the first signatory’s name and title (e.g., “John Doe, Attorney”).</li>
            <li>In the right column, type the second signatory’s name and title.</li>
            <li>Press <strong>Enter</strong> a few times above the names to create space for signatures.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Step 4: Remove Table Borders</h2>
        <ul class="steps">
            <li>Select the entire table.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Table Design</strong> > <strong>Borders</strong>.</li>
            <li>Select <strong>No Border</strong>.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Step 5: Final Adjustments and Saving</h2>
        <ul class="steps">
            <li>Ensure the spacing looks appropriate for signatures.</li>
            <li>Save the document as a **.docx** or **.pdf** as needed.</li>
            <li>Distribute the document with the formatted signature block.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
        <p>Using invisible two-column tables ensures that signature blocks remain aligned and professional in all legal documents.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<footer>
